The paper focuses on deep learning for gesture and action recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of attention models and recurrent neural networks also suggests a potential fit for artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the practical applications of the proposed method, including rapid prototyping and development, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or multimedia (cs.MM).
